# VinMarkdown

This is a fairly faithful port of [Craig Chockenberry's](https://furbo.org)
[MarkdownAttributedString](https://github.com/chockenberry/MarkdownAttributedString).

I needed some enhancements made to the original MarkdownAttributedString for [Zavala](https://github.com/vincode-io/Zavala). Because I was
struggling with the Objective-C in MarkdownAttributedString, I had [Claude](https://claude.ai) translate it to Swift. It was also supposed
to use [swift-markdown](https://github.com/apple/swift-markdown.git) for parsing and emitting. Claude and I even discussed this and agreed
together to use swift-markdown. Claude didn't use it.

This Swift fork of MarkdownAttributedString has some stuff specific to Zavala that may or may not work with what you are doing. There is
also some stuff missing. Claude analyzed Zavala and left out the parts of MarkdownAttributedString that Zavala wasn't dependent on. Everything
that deviates from MarkdownAttributedString was done by a hack and a robot. You get the idea.

You are assuredly better off using the original MarkdownAttributedString than this project. It is production proven with
[Tot](https://tot.rocks) and written by a brilliant programmer.
